Note that the kinetic-energy densities hold formula_17 everywhere because of the normalization. More significantly, the average kinetic energy is lowered by formula_18 by the deformation to .

Now, consider the potential energy. For definiteness, let us choose formula_19. Then it is clear that, outside the interval formula_6, the potential energy density is smaller for the because formula_21 there.

On the other hand, in the interval formula_6 we have
